title: Zhang In, Dong Out—Xi Wavers?

author: China Insights
description:
The CCP’s Fourth Plenum has opened, but China’s entire news system has gone “mute”: zero footage, zero dispatches, zero content. Xinhua ran a lone editorial, “Xinwen Lianbo” [CCTV’s main newscast] tiptoed around it, and the outside world is wondering—are the results undecided, are internal struggles deadlocked, or is this a deliberate pace-control? From state media’s silence to tremors in the military, this “meeting without images” has unveiled Zhongnanhai’s eeriest quiet.

title: Plenum Blackout: Is Xi Losing His Grip?

author: China Insights
description:
Three years ago, the scene of Hu Jintao being escorted out of the hall shocked the world; three years later, an AI video “recreates” that instant of power—this time, the one escorted away is Xi Jinping. As the Fourth Plenum reaches its climax, military purges, pressure from Party elders, and economic collapse intertwine into a storm. Will history truly repeat itself?
